00:35:12,508 --> 00:35:14,271
that's very clean...

253
00:35:14,510 --> 00:35:18,606
- and smells very nice.
- You don't have a pig in your kitchen.

254
00:35:20,649 --> 00:35:22,014
Yes, I do.

255
00:35:22,084 --> 00:35:25,212
I was just in there,
and I didn't see any goddamned pig.

256
00:35:25,287 --> 00:35:28,814
Don't move.
I'll get him.

257
00:35:30,792 --> 00:35:32,726
Piggy, where are you?

258
00:35:34,229 --> 00:35:36,197
There you are.

259
00:35:43,238 --> 00:35:46,207
Hi, Mathilda.

260
00:35:46,241 --> 00:35:48,971
Hi, piggy.

261
00:35:56,552 --> 00:35:59,715
How are you today?

262
00:35:59,788 --> 00:36:02,256
I've seen better days.

263
00:36:09,364 --> 00:36:14,199
- What's your name?
- Leon.

264
00:36:16,705 --> 00:36:18,764
Cute name.

265
00:36:25,747 --> 00:36:29,843
You have anyone to go to,
any family anyplace else?

266
00:36:40,963 --> 00:36:43,329
I'm gonna get some more milk.

267
00:37:02,050 --> 00:37:03,415
Holy shit.

268
00:37:09,625 --> 00:37:13,425
Don't touch that, please.

269
00:37:13,629 --> 00:37:15,961
What do you do for a living?

270
00:37:17,032 --> 00:37:18,431
Cleaner.

271
00:37:19,935 --> 00:37:21,869
You're a hit man?

272
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:26,964
Cool.

273
00:37:39,454 --> 00:37:44,016
- Do you clean anyone?
- No women, no kids. That's the rules.

274
00:37:44,092 --> 00:37:47,118
How much would it cost to hire someone
to get those dirtbags...

275
00:37:47,195 --> 00:37:50,028
who killed my brother?

276
00:37:50,098 --> 00:37:53,898
- Five grand a head.
- Wow.

277
00:37:53,969 --> 00:37:58,030
How about I work for you...

278
00:37:58,106 --> 00:38:01,667
and in exchange,
you teach me how to clean?

279
00:38:01,743 --> 00:38:04,803
What do you think?

280
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:06,905
I'll clean your place.
I'll do the shopping.

281
00:38:06,982 --> 00:38:09,177
I'll even wash your clothes.

282
00:38:10,385 --> 00:38:14,822
- Is it a deal?
- No, it's not a deal.

283
00:38:22,264 --> 00:38:27,133
What do you want me to do?
I've got no place to go.

284
00:38:27,202 --> 00:38:31,036
You've had a rough day today.

285
00:38:34,009 --> 00:38:36,409
Go to sleep,
and we'll see tomorrow.

286
00:38:50,959 --> 00:38:54,053
You've been really great
with me, Leon...

287
00:38:54,129 --> 00:38:57,155
and it's not always like that.

288
00:38:57,232 --> 00:38:59,097
You know?

289
00:39:06,875 --> 00:39:08,240
Good night.

290
00:40:24,553 --> 00:40:26,953
You sleep well?

291
00:40:26,988 --> 00:40:29,286
Good.

292
00:40:29,324 --> 00:40:31,849
- After breakfast you gotta take off.
- Where to?

293
00:40:31,927 --> 00:40:34,452
Not my problem.

294
00:40:48,944 --> 00:40:50,309
Read it.

295
00:40:57,219 --> 00:40:59,244
You don't know how to read.

296
00:40:59,321 --> 00:41:02,290
I'm learning, but I've had
a lot of work lately...

297
00:41:02,357 --> 00:41:05,417
so I'm a little behind.

298
00:41:05,493 --> 00:41:07,017
What's it say?

299
00:41:07,095 --> 00:41:11,122
I've decided what to do with my life.
I wanna be a cleaner.

300
00:41:11,199 --> 00:41:15,602
You wanna be a cleaner.
Here.

301
00:41:15,670 --> 00:41:20,471
Take it. It's a good-bye gift.
Go clean, but not with me.

302
00:41:20,508 --> 00:41:24,171
- I work alone. Understand?
- Bonnie and Clyde didn't work alone.

303
00:41:24,246 --> 00:41:27,238
Thelma and Louise didn't work alone.
They were the best.

304
00:41:29,384 --> 00:41:33,480
Mathilda, why are you
doing this to me?

305
00:41:33,521 --> 00:41:36,251
I've been nothing
but nice to you.

306
00:41:36,324 --> 00:41:39,225
I saved your life yesterday,
right outside the door.

307
00:41:39,261 --> 00:41:42,492
Right.
Now you're responsible for it.

308
00:41:42,530 --> 00:41:46,057
If you saved my life,
you must've saved it for a good reason.

309
00:41:46,134 --> 00:41:48,932
If you throw me out now,
it's like you never opened your door...

310
00:41:49,004 --> 00:41:51,700
like you let me die
right there in front of it.

311
00:41:51,907 --> 00:41:57,243
But you did open it. So...

312
00:42:00,482 --> 00:42:04,942
If you don't help me,
I'll die tonight. I can feel it.

313
00:42:05,020 --> 00:42:07,215
I don't wanna die tonight.

314
00:42:09,691 --> 00:42:12,216
You're just a little girl.

315
00:42:12,294 --> 00:42:15,263
Don't take it badly,
but I don't think you could do it.

316
00:42:15,297 --> 00:42:16,662
I'm sorry.

317
00:42:35,450 --> 00:42:37,418
How's that?

318
00:43:11,353 --> 00:43:14,413
Don't you ever do that again
or I'll break your head.

319
00:43:14,489 --> 00:43:16,013
You got that?

320
00:43:17,225 --> 00:43:20,592
I don't work like that.
It's not professional.

321
00:43:20,628 --> 00:43:22,596
There is rules.

322
00:43:23,631 --> 00:43:26,464
And stop saying "okay"
all the time!

323
00:43:29,504 --> 00:43:31,165
Good.

324
00:43:46,388 --> 00:43:48,583
You expect to use that
in this hotel?

325
00:43:50,558 --> 00:43:53,618
Mister, I have to use it...

326
00:43:53,661 --> 00:43:57,757
because I have an audition
at Juilliard next month...

327
00:43:57,832 --> 00:44:00,164
and I have to practice.

328
00:44:00,235 --> 00:44:04,137
Okay, but not after 10:00.

329
00:44:04,205 --> 00:44:06,230
- I promise.
- All right.

330
00:44:08,243 --> 00:44:11,212
I'll put you
at the end of the hall...

331
00:44:11,279 --> 00:44:15,340
so that you
don't disturb anyone.

332
00:44:15,417 --> 00:44:16,816
Fill those out, please.

333
00:44:21,156 --> 00:44:26,150
Daddy, can I please fill them out?
I like to check in to hotels.

334
00:44:29,597 --> 00:44:31,758
Thanks, Pop.
I'll bring these back in a minute.

335
00:44:31,833 --> 00:44:34,199
Fourth floor!

336
00:44:34,269 --> 00:44:35,759
Thanks, mister!

337
00:44:35,837 --> 00:44:39,068
You're lucky to have a little girl
that's interested in things.

338
00:44:41,376 --> 00:44:44,777
I have a kid, 17,
does nothing all day long.

339
00:44:50,452 --> 00:44:53,512
Can I leave my plant here
while I take my stuff upstairs?

340
00:44:53,555 --> 00:44:55,386
Of course.

341
00:45:16,344 --> 00:45:19,541
I'm putting in a name of a girl
in my class who makes me sick.

342
00:45:22,183 --> 00:45:25,619
If things get hot,
she'll take the heat.

343
00:45:42,604 --> 00:45:45,300
There. Finished.

344
00:45:45,773 --> 00:45:48,765
- How old are you?
- Eighteen.

345
00:45:49,611 --> 00:45:52,603
- Eighteen?
- Want to see my license?

346
00:45:53,648 --> 00:45:57,880
No. You just look a little young.

347
00:45:58,686 --> 00:46:00,415
Thanks.

348
00:46:07,595 --> 00:46:11,224
Leon, I want you to teach me
how to be like you.

349
00:46:11,299 --> 00:46:13,494
I want to be strong and smart
like you.

350
00:46:15,336 --> 00:46:18,169
I know I'm not
strong enough yet...

351
00:46:18,239 --> 00:46:22,266
but I could learn the basics,
the theory.

352
00:46:22,343 --> 00:46:26,473
What do you think?
Just the theory.

353
00:46:26,514 --> 00:46:28,744
I need this, Leon.

354
00:46:30,518 --> 00:46:32,611
I need time
to get my head together.

355
00:46:32,654 --> 00:46:35,487
Yeah, and I need...

356
00:46:41,262 --> 00:46:42,695
a drink.

357
00:46:42,764 --> 00:46:45,756
Don't move.
I'll go get one.

358
00:47:10,858 --> 00:47:14,350
When you told me
to get this baby out for you...

359
00:47:14,429 --> 00:47:16,659
I thought my hearin' was goin'.

360
00:47:16,731 --> 00:47:21,634
I says to myself, " Leon's a pro.
Nobody uses that except beginners."

361
00:47:21,703 --> 00:47:23,500
I like to stay in shape.

362
00:47:23,538 --> 00:47:27,941
Sure.
Always stay on top of it.

363
00:47:28,009 --> 00:47:31,740
It's like me. I gotta know
where everything is all the time.

364
00:47:31,813 --> 00:47:34,441
I never leave this place,
except to go from here to there.

365
00:47:37,785 --> 00:47:40,777
Change ain't good, Leon.
You know?

366
00:47:51,733 --> 00:47:53,257
Check it.

367
00:47:54,769 --> 00:47:57,465
- Make sure it's the right thing.
- I trust you.

368
00:47:57,538 --> 00:48:00,530
One thing's got nothin' to do
with the other. Remember that.

369
00:48:01,909 --> 00:48:03,843
I will.

370
00:48:18,893 --> 00:48:21,862
The rifle is the first weapon
you learn how to use...

371
00:48:21,929 --> 00:48:25,763
because it lets you
keep your distance from the client.

372
00:48:25,833 --> 00:48:28,028
The closer you get
to being a pro...

373
00:48:28,102 --> 00:48:31,401
the closer you can get
to the client.

374
00:48:31,472 --> 00:48:34,908
The knife, for example,
is the last thing you learn.

375
00:48:40,648 --> 00:48:42,013
Position.

376
00:49:06,341 --> 00:49:10,004
Never take it off until the last minute.
It reflects light.

377
00:49:10,078 --> 00:49:12,911
They can see you coming
from a mile away.

378
00:49:12,980 --> 00:49:16,746
And always dress down.

379
00:49:16,818 --> 00:49:19,912
Never brighter
than the floor, okay?

380
00:49:22,824 --> 00:49:27,488
Let's practice now.
It's the best way to learn.

381
00:49:27,562 --> 00:49:29,621
Who should I hit?

382
00:49:29,697 --> 00:49:31,358
Whoever.

383
00:49:38,139 --> 00:49:40,505
I'll be with you in a second.
Give me a few minutes. Thank you.

384
00:49:40,575 --> 00:49:43,373
You guys get lost.
I don't want to see you.

385
00:49:43,444 --> 00:49:46,811
- Is everyone in position?
- This has to look natural.

386
00:49:56,457 --> 00:49:59,824
- No women, no kids. Right?
- Right.

387
00:50:07,068 --> 00:50:09,536
Jogger in the yellow and orange?

388
00:50:14,041 --> 00:50:16,532
Keep calm.

389
00:50:19,747 --> 00:50:23,205
Don't take your eyes off him.

390
00:50:23,451 --> 00:50:25,112
Breathe easy.

391
00:50:26,921 --> 00:50:28,582
Watch his movement.

392
00:50:31,058 --> 00:50:33,549
Pretend you're running with him.

393
00:50:36,597 --> 00:50:39,691
Try to feel his next movement.

394
00:50:41,202 --> 00:50:44,638
Take a deep breath.
Hold it.

395
00:50:53,114 --> 00:50:54,672
Now.

396
00:50:54,749 --> 00:50:56,580
Oh, my God!

397
00:50:56,651 --> 00:51:00,212
- I'm all right. I'm fine.
- Get down! Where'd that come from?

398
00:51:00,455 --> 00:51:04,084
One shot. Not bad, huh?

399
00:51:04,158 --> 00:51:06,683
- Who the hell fired?
- I just can't breathe! Get off me.

400
00:51:06,761 --> 00:51:10,458
Can we try
with real bullets now?

401
00:51:10,531 --> 00:51:12,499
Not today.
Let's pack up.

402
00:51:21,809 --> 00:51:23,174
Like that.

403
00:52:05,686 --> 00:52:08,951
- No, thanks.
- No discussion.

404
00:52:50,731 --> 00:52:52,699
"It seemed...

405
00:52:54,035 --> 00:52:56,003
to Socrates..."

406
00:53:03,844 --> 00:53:05,778
I'll do it.

407
00:53:19,794 --> 00:53:22,194
Leon, all we do is work.

408
00:53:22,263 --> 00:53:25,357
We need a break.
Let's play a game.

409
00:53:25,600 --> 00:53:29,161
- What kind of game?
- I have this great game.

410
00:53:29,236 --> 00:53:33,070
It makes you think and helps your
memory. It's exactly what you need.

411
00:53:46,387 --> 00:53:48,048
Like a virgin

412
00:53:49,924 --> 00:53:53,189
Touched for the very first time

413
00:53:57,765 --> 00:54:00,791
- Who is it?
- I don't know.

414
00:54:10,945 --> 00:54:16,781
Happy birthday to you

415
00:54:16,817 --> 00:54:21,083
Happy birthday, Mr. President

416
00:54:21,122 --> 00:54:23,647
I don't know.

417
00:54:32,333 --> 00:54:34,198
Moustache.

418
00:54:38,205 --> 00:54:41,800
I'm singing in the rain

419
00:54:41,876 --> 00:54:44,367
Just singing in the rain

420
00:54:44,445 --> 00:54:47,073
- What a beaut...
- Gene Kelly?

421
00:54:48,749 --> 00:54:50,114
Good.

422
00:54:50,151 --> 00:54:53,018
Your turn now.

423
00:54:58,459 --> 00:55:00,256
Okay, pilgrim.

424
00:55:03,764 --> 00:55:05,163
Clint Eastwood?

425
00:55:12,039 --> 00:55:17,136
- I don't know. I give up.
- John Wayne.

426
00:55:17,211 --> 00:55:21,170
I was just about to say that.
I swear. It's amazing.

427
00:55:21,248 --> 00:55:23,716
Leon, really brilliant.

428
00:55:26,053 --> 00:55:28,021
Amazing.

429
00:55:42,937 --> 00:55:47,169
- You love your plant, don't you?
- It's my best friend.

430
00:55:47,241 --> 00:55:50,870
Always happy.
No questions.

431
00:55:52,379 --> 00:55:55,439
It's like me, you see.

432
00:55:55,516 --> 00:55:57,814
No roots.

433
00:55:57,885 --> 00:56:01,514
If you really love it, you should
plant it in a park so it can have roots.

434
00:56:05,760 --> 00:56:08,285
You should be watering me
if you want me to grow.

435
00:56:10,498 --> 00:56:12,022
You're right.

436
00:56:23,410 --> 00:56:24,900
Wait!

437
00:56:39,593 --> 00:56:44,257
They gotta be jumping out of the plate.
They gotta be alive.

438
00:56:52,339 --> 00:56:54,807
It's been a long time, Leon.

439
00:57:00,581 --> 00:57:02,549
I missed you.

440
00:57:02,616 --> 00:57:07,451
- And you missed some nice jobs too.
- Been training.

441
00:57:07,521 --> 00:57:11,514
Training's good,
but don't overdo it.

442
00:57:11,592 --> 00:57:14,083
Training don't pay
as good as working, Leon.

443
00:57:14,128 --> 00:57:15,527
Tony...

444
00:57:18,465 --> 00:57:23,129
all the money I make,
that you keep for me...

445
00:57:23,204 --> 00:57:25,195
You need some money?

446
00:57:25,272 --> 00:57:26,899
Just curious.

447
00:57:26,974 --> 00:57:28,908
I've been working
a long time...

448
00:57:28,976 --> 00:57:32,537
and I haven't done anything
with my money.

449
00:57:34,648 --> 00:57:40,450
I thought maybe
someday I could use it.

450
00:57:40,521 --> 00:57:42,989
You met a woman.

451
00:57:52,499 --> 00:57:54,558
You gotta be careful
with women.

452
00:57:54,635 --> 00:57:57,604
Remember when you arrived
in this country?

453
00:57:57,671 --> 00:58:02,165
When I took you in, you were still wet
behind the fuckin' ears...

454
00:58:02,209 --> 00:58:05,178
and, already, you were in deep shit
because of a woman.

455
00:58:05,212 --> 00:58:10,149
- Don't forget that, Leon.
- I wish I could sometimes.

456
00:58:12,653 --> 00:58:15,053
You know, about my money...

457
00:58:15,122 --> 00:58:19,456
Maybe I could give...

458
00:58:19,526 --> 00:58:21,585
a little...

459
00:58:23,197 --> 00:58:25,461
to someone.

460
00:58:25,532 --> 00:58:28,592
You know, to help out.

461
00:58:31,205 --> 00:58:35,232
It's your money. I'm just
holding it for you, like a bank.

462
00:58:35,309 --> 00:58:39,609
Except better than a bank
because banks always get knocked off.

463
00:58:39,680 --> 00:58:42,114
No one knocks off old Tony.

464
00:58:42,182 --> 00:58:44,616
Besides, with a bank...

465
00:58:44,685 --> 00:58:48,052
there's always tons of forms
and all that shit.

466
00:58:48,122 --> 00:58:53,185
But old Tony, nothin' to read,
nothin' to write. It's all in his head.

467
00:58:54,461 --> 00:58:57,726
I know how to read now.

468
00:58:57,965 --> 00:59:01,059
That's good, Leon.

469
00:59:04,004 --> 00:59:05,494
Your money's here.

470
00:59:05,572 --> 00:59:08,302
Whenever you want it,
you just ask me.

471
00:59:08,375 --> 00:59:12,402
- Here's a grand. Come on.
- It's okay. I don't need it.

472
00:59:12,479 --> 00:59:17,041
- Take it. Have some fun. Go ahead.
- Thank you.

473
00:59:17,117 --> 00:59:21,019
All right.
Now let's talk business.

474
00:59:21,088 --> 00:59:24,524
Don't move.
I'll go get the file.

475
00:59:24,591 --> 00:59:28,652
Manolo, a glass of milk
for my friend Leon here.

476
00:59:52,052 --> 00:59:54,418
Listen, Mathilda,
you better be careful.

477
00:59:54,455 --> 00:59:57,117
You can't just speak
to any guy off the street.

478
00:59:58,325 --> 01:00:01,123
Leon, get a grip.
What's the big fucking deal?

479
01:00:01,195 --> 01:00:03,993
I was just smoking a butt
while I was waiting.

480
01:00:05,632 --> 01:00:07,998
I want you to stop cursing.

481
01:00:08,068 --> 01:00:10,263
You can't talk to people
like that all the time.

482
01:00:10,337 --> 01:00:13,431
I want you to make an effort
to talk nice.

483
01:00:18,212 --> 01:00:21,409
And I want you to stop smoking.
It will kill you.

484
01:00:28,088 --> 01:00:30,716
Stay away from him.
He looks like a weirdo.

485
01:00:35,796 --> 01:00:39,596
I'll be out in five minutes.
Stand where I can see you.

486
01:00:53,113 --> 01:00:57,277
Leon, I think I'm kinda
falling in love with you.

487
01:00:59,753 --> 01:01:03,189
It's the first time for me,
you know.

488
01:01:03,223 --> 01:01:06,522
How do you know it's love
if you've never been in love before?

489
01:01:06,593 --> 01:01:09,494
'Cause I feel it.

490
01:01:09,530 --> 01:01:11,191
Where?

491
01:01:14,701 --> 01:01:16,669
In my stomach.

492
01:01:19,573 --> 01:01:23,134
It's all warm.

493
01:01:23,210 --> 01:01:28,375
I always had a knot there,
and now it's gone.

494
01:01:31,318 --> 01:01:36,551
Mathilda, I'm glad you
don't have a stomachache anymore.

495
01:01:36,590 --> 01:01:39,150
I don't think
it means anything.

496
01:01:39,226 --> 01:01:43,094
I'm late for work.
I hate being late for work.

497
01:02:27,441 --> 01:02:29,432
How's the practicing going?

498
01:02:59,406 --> 01:03:04,503
- How are we today, miss?
- A little sick of practicing.

499
01:03:04,578 --> 01:03:06,512
I understand.

500
01:03:06,580 --> 01:03:08,514
But you're doing all right.

501
01:03:08,582 --> 01:03:10,573
I haven't received
any complaints.

502
01:03:10,651 --> 01:03:14,849
I put a cloth over the strings
to lessen the noise.

503
01:03:15,989 --> 01:03:17,581
That's very smart.

504
